<REFENTRY ID="baselib---sigpause-1"> <REFMETA>
<REFENTRYTITLE>__sigpause</REFENTRYTITLE>
<REFMISCINFO>Base Libraries</REFMISCINFO>
</REFMETA>
<REFNAMEDIV>
<REFNAME>__sigpause</REFNAME>
<REFPURPOSE>
atomically release blocked signals and wait for interrupt
</REFPURPOSE>
</REFNAMEDIV>
<REFSYNOPSISDIV>
<REFSYNOPSISDIVINFO>
<DATE>16 February 2001</DATE>
</REFSYNOPSISDIVINFO>
<SYNOPSIS>
int __sigpause(int sig_or_mask, int is_sig);
</SYNOPSIS>
</REFSYNOPSISDIV>
<REFSECT1>
<REFSECT1INFO>
<DATE>16 February 2001</DATE>
</REFSECT1INFO>
<TITLE>Description
</TITLE>
<PARA>
__sigpause(sig_or_mask, is_sig) has the same behavior as sigpause(sig_or_mask, is_sig) as specified by X/Open.
</PARA>
<PARA>
__sigpause is not in the source standard; it is only in the binary standard.
</PARA>
</REFSECT1>
</REFENTRY>
